<task id="installation-instructions-all-platforms">
  <title>Install Using the All Platforms Installer</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Installation <indexterm>all platforms version</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>To install using the all platforms installer, follow these steps:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step id="install-all.step1">
        <cmd>Download the all platforms installation package (<ph product="editor"
              ><filepath>oxygen.tar.gz</filepath>
          </ph><ph product="author"><filepath>oxygenAuthor.tar.gz</filepath></ph><ph
            product="developer"><filepath>oxygenDeveloper.tar.gz</filepath></ph><ph
            product="svnClient"><filepath>syncroSVNClient.tar.gz</filepath></ph>) to a folder of
          your choice.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="install-all.step2">
        <cmd>Extract the archive in that folder.</cmd>
        <stepresult><ph keyref="product"/> is now installed in a new sub-folder called <filepath
            product="editor">oxygen</filepath><filepath product="author"
            >oxygenAuthor</filepath><filepath product="developer"
            >oxygenDeveloper</filepath><filepath product="svnClient"
          >syncroSVNClient</filepath>.</stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="install-all.step4">
        <cmd>Optionally, you can move the directory where you installed <ph keyref="product"/> to
          your applications directory. You can also rename it to contain the product version
          information. For example, you can rename it as <filepath product="editor"
              ><keyword>oxygen</keyword></filepath><filepath product="author"
              ><keyword>oxygenAuthor</keyword></filepath><filepath product="developer"
              ><keyword>oxygenDeveloper</keyword></filepath><filepath product="svnClient"
              ><keyword>syncroSVNClient</keyword></filepath><keyword keyref="minorVersion"/>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd id="install-all.step5">Start <ph keyref="product"/> by running <ph product="editor"
              ><filepath>oxygen.XXX</filepath></ph><ph product="author"
              ><filepath>oxygenAuthor.XXX</filepath></ph><ph product="developer"
              ><filepath>oxygenDeveloper.XXX</filepath></ph><ph product="svnClient"
              ><filepath>syncroSVNClient.XXX</filepath></ph>, which is located in the install
          folder. </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="install-all.step6">
        <cmd>To license your copy of <ph keyref="product"/> go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Help</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Register</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and enter your <xref keyref="install_license-key">license
            information</xref>.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
